{"questionId":"9084664","questionHtml":"<p>Kepler’s Third law relates the orbital period <em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi></math></em> of a planet about its sun to its orbital radius <em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi></math></em>. The mass of the Sun is <em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>M</mi></math>.</em></p>\n<p>What is a correct algebraic form of the law?</p>\n<p><br>A.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>G</mi><mi>M</mi></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></msup></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mi>G</mi><mi>M</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>67</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>G</mi><mi>M</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>67</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mi>G</mi><mi>M</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>A</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9084664","referenceCode":"EXE.1A.SL.TZ0.14","subjectId":"59-dp-physics-first-assessment-2025","title":"Kepler’s Third law relates the orbital period T of a planet about its sun to its orbital radius r. The mass of the Sun is M. What is a correct algebraic form of the law? A. T=2πr1.","paper":"1A","level":"SL","questionNumber":"14","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["D. Fields","D. Fields","D.1 Gravitational fields"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}